rules: Rule1: If a researcher withdraws a paper, then the researcher revises the paper.
Rule2: Provided that an innovation is patented for a process, the innovation is licensed to a company.
Rule3: Under the condition that an innovation is patented for a process, it is not the case that the innovation is licensed to a company.
Rule4: Either an innovation is patented for a process, or ethics approves a study, or a grant funds a project, or the project is successful.
Rule5: Either a funder renews a grant, or if a regulator halts a trial, the regulator investigates a violation.
Rule6: Provided that a funder terminates a grant, the funder does not renew the grant.
Rule7: Under the condition that a funder suspends a grant, the funder does not renew the grant.
Rule8: Whenever a funder audits finances, the funder terminates a grant.
Rule9: Either a funder audits finances or a funder reviews progress.
Rule10: If a funder reviews progress, then the funder suspends a grant.
Rule11: Provided that a scientist discovers a compound, the compound is tested for efficacy.
Rule12: Whenever a scientist discovers a compound, the compound is applied as a treatment.
Rule13: Either a scientist discovers a compound or a scientist isolates a molecule.
Rule14: If a scientist isolates a molecule, then the project is successful.
Rule15: Under the condition that results are published in a journal, the project is successful.
Rule16: Provided that a company acquires a patent, the company markets a product.
Rule17: Either a company acquires a patent or a company develops a formulation.
Rule18: Under the condition that a company develops a formulation, if the project is not successful, then it is not the case that a plant develops food.
Rule19: Provided that a sample is contaminated by a pathogen, it is not the case that a plant develops food.
Rule20: Under the condition that a lab is certified for a standard, an authority accredits the lab.

Rule21: Either a publication validates research, or if it is not the case that if a platform publishes a publication then it is not the case that a plant develops food, then a publication delays a time period.
Rule22: If a researcher receives funding, then a grant funds a project.
Rule23: Provided that a researcher collaborates with an institution, the project is successful.
Rule24: If a grant is extended for a period, then if it is not the case that if a project accelerates a timeline then the project delays a timeline, then the project completes a deadline.
Rule25: Either a grant is extended for a period or a grant is renewed for funding.
Rule26: Whenever a grant is renewed for funding, then if it is not the case that if a project accelerates a timeline then the project delays a timeline, then the project completes a deadline.
Rule27: Provided that research infringes on a patent, it is not the case that an innovation is patented for a process.
Rule28: Under the condition that research violates an agreement, research does not license a technology.
Rule29: If a study replicates results, then the study confirms a hypothesis.
Rule30: Either a peer critiques a methodology or a peer supports findings.
Rule31: If a peer supports findings, then if a study replicates results, it is not the case that the study confirms a hypothesis.
Rule32: Provided that a peer challenges conclusions, whenever a study replicates results, the study does not confirm a hypothesis.
Rule33: Under the condition that an author responds to a critique, if a peer critiques a methodology, then the peer challenges conclusions.
Rule34: Either an author responds to a critique or an author revises a paper.
Rule35: Whenever an author revises a paper, then if a peer critiques a methodology, the peer challenges conclusions.
Rule36: If a compound treats a disease, then the project is successful.

Rule37: Provided that a researcher modifies a protocol, if it is not the case that if a compound is applied as a treatment then the compound treats a disease, then the treatment does not fail a trial.
Rule38: Either a researcher modifies a protocol or a researcher repeats an experiment.

Rule39: Either a review invalidates a study, or if a researcher repeats an experiment, then if it is not the case that if a compound is applied as a treatment then the compound treats a disease, then the treatment does not fail a trial.
Rule40: Provided that a researcher defends work, it is not the case that a review invalidates a study.
Rule41: Under the condition that a researcher clarifies methods, the review does not invalidate the study.
Rule42: Whenever a researcher presents at a conference, the researcher defends work.
Rule43: Either a researcher presents at a conference or a researcher publishes a response.
Rule44: Provided that a researcher publishes a response, the researcher clarifies methods.
Rule45: If research analyzes data, then food is distributed to a market.
Rule46: Provided that it is not the case that if a scientist discovers a compound then the project is successful, a study replicates results.
Rule47: Under the condition that it is not the case that if a compound is tested for efficacy then results are published in a journal, a journal retracts a paper.
Rule48: Whenever it is not the case that if a company markets a product then the company commercializes a product, the company recalls a product.
Rule49: If it is not the case that if a company markets a product then the company commercializes a product, then it is not the case that the company recalls a product.
Rule50: Provided that it is not the case that if a lab sterilizes equipment then the lab quarantines a sample, a pathogen spreads in a facility.
Rule51: Under the condition that it is not the case that if an authority accredits a lab then it is not the case that a pathogen spreads in a facility, the authority closes the lab.
Rule52: Provided that it is not the case that either a researcher receives funding or a researcher collaborates with an institution, the project accelerates a timeline.
Rule53: Under the condition that it is not the case that if a project accelerates a timeline then the project delays a timeline, it is not the case that the project completes a deadline.
Rule54: Whenever it is not the case that if a compound is applied as a treatment then the compound treats a disease, the treatment fails a trial.
Rule55: If it is not the case that if a researcher submits a paper then a journal accepts the paper, the researcher withdraws the paper.
Rule56: Whenever it is not the case that if a researcher submits a paper then a journal accepts the paper, it is not the case that the researcher revises the paper.
Rule57: Provided that it is not the case that if it is not the case that if the project is not successful then a plant cultivates food then research analyzes data, the researcher submits a paper.
Rule58: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the project is not successful then a regulator monitors a trial, the regulator halts the trial.
Rule59: Provided that it is not the case that if the project is not successful then a sample is contaminated by a pathogen, the lab sterilizes equipment.
Rule60: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the project is not successful then a sample is contaminated by a pathogen, it is not the case that the lab quarantines the sample.
Rule61: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the project is not successful then a plant cultivates food, it is not the case that food is distributed to a market.
Rule62: Whenever it is not the case that research infringes on a patent, research licenses a technology.
Rule63: Provided that the project is not successful, a plant develops food.
Rule64: If the project is not successful, a platform publishes a publication.
Rule65: If the project is not successful, a regulator does not monitor a trial.

Fact3: It is not the case that a grant funds a project.

Fact7: A company does not commercialize a product.
Fact8: A publication does not delay a time period.
Fact9: A publication does not validate research.
Fact10: An authority does not close a lab.
Fact11: A project does not delay a timeline.
Fact12: A plant does not cultivate food.
